author: National Geographic
description:
On the 24th anniversary of September 11, 2001, National Geographic presents a special mega episode that uncovers the global and personal stories of a day that changed the world forever.

9/11: Control the Skies
4,500 planes are in the air over North America when the second jet strikes the Twin Towers of the World Trade Center on September 11, 2001. The FAA declares ATC Zero, no planes in US airspace.  

9/11: Where Were You? Never Forget
Survivors of the 9/11 attacks recount their harrowing stories of the day and describe how they’ve found ways to heal more than 20 years later.

Bin Laden's Hard Drive
Newly declassified hard drives taken from the compound where Osama bin Laden was killed reveal a groundbreaking look at his personal life.

9/11: Missing Carmen Rivera
Luis Rivera believed his wife Carmen survived the 9/11 attacks at the World Trade Center in New York. This is the story of his search for her.
